         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="4"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>ñäktaśśi</w><w>śāp</w><w>tāṣäl<surplus>ä</surplus></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>yal</w><w>säs</w><w>mā</w><w>te</w><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ā</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>rä</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>m</w><w>p<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>lkässi</w><w>mā</w><w>cä</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>puk</w><w>pättāñäktañ</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="3"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he is to put a curse on the gods ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is to be done. He ... not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to torment (?) ... not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... all Buddhas ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408g"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408i"/>.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>tāṣäl</hi>: the akṣara <distinct type="ms_text">_ṣ_a</distinct> is relatively secure; the <distinct type="ms_text">_l</distinct> is only compatible with the traces, other restorations would also be possible.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">_s_a</distinct>: a faint cross is visible on top, but if an akṣara was added below the line, it is now completely lost.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">/// [m] p·_l_k_assi</distinct>: the likely restorations seem to be <hi>(ca)m p(ä)lkässi</hi> 'to torment him' or <hi>(tā)m p(ä)lkässi</hi> 'to torment her'. However, we have to assume that the spelling was <distinct type="ms_text">mpä</distinct> with the vowel sign <hi>ä</hi> instead of expected <distinct type="ms_text">m_p_a</distinct> with Fremdzeichen (the alternative <distinct type="ms_text">_m_p_a</distinct> is rare anyhow).</note></p>
         </div>
